			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Weekly News Review from a Christian Viewpoint.  Patrick Woodward talks to <strong>Laura Webster</strong>,  Head of Policy at the aid agency <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outbound/article/www.tearfund.org');" href="http://www.tearfund.org/" target="_blank">Tearfund</a> about the latest news from a Christian standpoint. Today, what&#8217;s special about a<em> Christian</em> aid agency as many rush to help victims of the Indonesian earthquake?  There&#8217;s a new food crisis looming in East Africa &#8211; what&#8217;s to be done?  And the labour party&#8217;s woes at being dropped by the Sun.</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Story Links:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Sumatran quake:<a href="http://revivalmedia.org/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/quake.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1492" title=" telegraph.co.uk" src="http://revivalmedia.org/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/quake.jpg" alt=" telegraph.co.uk" width="112" height="71" /></a></strong></p>
